# Monorepo Structure Context

## Active Layout (authoritative)

- Runnable applications live in `./applications`.
- Reusable libraries live in `./packages`.
- Tooling and scripts may live in `./tools`.
- Libraries must not import from `./applications`.
- Internal package scope is `@aor/*`.

## Bounded Context Library Shape

- Preferred BC package family:
  - `./packages/{bc}/types`
  - `./packages/{bc}/write`
  - `./packages/{bc}/read`
- Optional packages are allowed when justified:
  - `./packages/{bc}/core`
  - `./packages/{bc}/write-domain`
  - `./packages/{bc}/read-domain`

## Integration Package

- `./packages/integration` is the dedicated cross-BC adapter composition package.
- Applications may import `@aor/integration`.
- BC packages must not import from `@aor/integration`.

## CQRS and Source Organization

- Keep read and write responsibilities separated.
- Prefer aggregate-first organization under `src/domains/{aggregate}/` when working inside BC packages.
- Keep command/event artifacts atomic (one intent per file).
